This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as entailment, coreference, relation extraction, and question answering. It also proposes a new method for hypernymy detection using vector embeddings, which is a common technique in NLP. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves supervised and unsupervised learning methods for hypernymy detection. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the task of relation extraction, which is a common task in IR. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new method for representing words as non-negative vector embeddings, which is a fundamental data structure in NLP.
